propInfo.ownerExprience: As at all our communities, our services are grounded in our belief in nurturing the body, mind and spirit of our residents through a holistic approach to wellness.
propInfo.careServicesOther: Memory Care neighborhood grounded in the "I'm Still Here" Philosophy, which focuses on what a person can do and learn vs. what he/she may have lost.

propInfo.staffDescription: Fully licensed staff are on-site 24 hours per day.  Employee engagement ratings consistently exceed company Gold Standards and continue to improve every year. We pride ourselves in providing excellent care and service and know happy staff translates to very satisfied residents.
propInfo.communityDescription: Situated adjacent to St. Thomas More Church, this proximity to the church and school allows for intergenerational activities that enrich the lives of both residents and students. With a focus on best-in-class quality care, as well as lifestyle amenities, including restaurant-style dining, a robust library, an accessible computer lab and a lively gathering room bustling with activities, AlmaVia of San Francisco focuses on the holistic wellness of its residents.

attributes.communityDescription: Alma Via Of San Francisco is an assisted living community located in San Francisco, CA. This is a large sized assisted living community with 135 units. Communities this size typically offer 1-bedroom apartments, multiple levels of care, restaurant style dining, and a robust resident enrichment program. The listed community cost is $6,995 per month which is around 18% over the average of $5,950 in San Francisco. The community is managed by Elder Care Alliance. The community has an average star rating of 4.18 from 50 reviews. One reviewer says: "I visited Alma Via yesterday for a meeting and the facility was amazing.
